  <h2>Patterns in Conway's Game of life</h2>


  <p> Conway's Game of life rules can be summarised as : </p>
  
  <ul> 
    <li> Patterns for which it can be proved that the population grows without limit shouldn't exist </li>
    <li> Patterns that apparently grow without limit should exist </li>
    <li> Patterns that change for a period of time before coming to an end after: </li>
      <ul>
        <li> all the cells have died </li>
        <li> the cells have settled into a stable configuration (that doesn't change or that oscillates) </li>
      </ul>
  </ul> 

  <p> Patterns that occur in the Game of life include: </p>
      <ul>
        <li> static patterns (still) </li>
        <li> repeating patters (oscillators) </li>
        <li> patterns that move on board (spaceships) </li>
      </ul>

<br>

  <h2>Still</h2>

  
    <p> A pattern which does not change from one generation to the next is known as a still life. </p>
    <p> It can also be thought of as an oscilator with unit period. </p>


