<br>

  <h2 style="clear:both">Oscillator</h2>


    <p> A pattern that returns to its original state after a finite number of generations is called an oscillator. </p>
    <p> Conway originally believed that no pattern could produce an infinite number of cells, but many counterexamples were found in the end. </p>
    <p> If the configuration doesn't move it is called an oscillator, otherwise it is called a glider/spaceship. It is not known whether oscillators of periods 19, 23, 38, 41, 43 and 53 exist, but it is strongly believed that they do. </p>
  <p> An interesting fact is that the blinker is the only known one cell thick oscillator.  </p>


  <div class="alloscimages">
   
    <div class="imageOsc">
      <p id="imageExp">blinker / toad / beacon</p>  <img src="osc.png" height="150" width="300">
    </div> 
